  description: nown locally as the lindog, is a possibly extinct species of cyprinid
    fish endemic to Lake Lanao in Mindanao, the Philippines where it prefers shallow,
    weedy waters of the bays. This species can reach a length of 13.2 centimetres
    (5.2 in) TL. It is commercially important to local peoples as a food fish
